ENNt6pbVynwggDTyf7uulk1RUnQ_UiYA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:218;s:6:"height";i:232;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/75083518773686180/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:66:{i:0;s:87:"If your garage door opener is clicking it is probably also flashing a light on and off.";i:1;s:66:"If this is the case you have likely locked your opener by mistake.";i:2;s:152:"A lot of homeowners will accidentally put their opener into lock mode by sliding a switch or holding a lock button too long on the wall control station.";i:3;s:81:"A faulty circuit board will cause the garage door opener to make clicking sounds.";i:4;s:78:"Also the opener may work sometimes but on other occasions it does not respond.";i:5;s:154:"A power outage or surge -- particularly one that results from a storm -- may either cause a temporary malfunction or permanently damage the circuit board.";i:6;s:103:"A power outage or power surge caused by a recent storm can destroy the circuit board causing the issue.";i:7;s:92:"Worn Garage Door Rollers More often than not the cause if a clicking garage door opener may.";i:8;s:134:"If your motor reverses and flashes 10 times this is its way of saying Its not making a good connection between the two safety sensors.";i:9;s:78:"You will have to re-position clean rewire or replace your garage door sensors.";i:10;s:68:"On the bottom of the garage door rails there are two safety sensors.";i:11;s:82:"Ive unplugged it like before waited 10 minutes and plugged it back in and nothing.";i:12;s:133:"Not a sound from the motor just what I believe is a relay clicking when I push either the remote control or the wall mounted control.";i:13;s:61:"The safety sensors for the garage door are not blockedhave a.";i:14;s:43:"There is an led light up on the motor head.";i:15;s:65:"If this is flashing in succession resubmit with this information.";i:16;s:132:"If this is flashing 5 times it is more than likely opened too far and is stuck on the up stop bolt or the rpm sensor needs replaced.";i:17;s:99:"If you can hold the wall button down and the door activates then the problem is the safety sensors.";i:18;s:102:"Last night I opened the door and then went to close the door and we can just hear a click in the unit.";i:19;s:74:"Disconnected the garage door from the track and still have the same click.";i:20;s:71:"Then later on that night the garage door seemed to be functioning fine.";i:21;s:53:"Tested it out a few times and appeared to be working.";i:22;s:90:"Then this morning I opened the garage door left the garage and went to close the door and.";i:23;s:97:"My Genie ProStealth garage door opener is clicking and light comes on however it will not engage.";i:24;s:62:"How can I troubleshoot to determine what the problem might be.";i:25;s:112:"I have switched out the main boards in the units and the problem stays in the unit and did not follow the board.";i:26;s:55:"Units are only 10 years old and I would like to repair.";i:27;s:107:"My 13 horse liftmaster garage door stopped working it only clicks when I use the remote or the wall opener.";i:28;s:112:"The motor doesnt hum like it is trying to open just a clicking sound comes from the unit and the light comes on.";i:29;s:38:"Suggestions thanks for the assistance.";i:30;s:111:"A very common symptom of a bad circuit board is a clicking sound coming from the garage door opener motor head.";i:31;s:159:"Sometimes it will be a single click and other times you will hear multiple clicks in no particular order and the light bulb will begin to flash erratically as.";i:32;s:69:"To unlock your garage door opener push the lock button for 5 seconds.";i:33;s:79:"Once you push this button the light on the garage door opener will flash twice.";i:34;s:77:"Once you see the double flash press the control button on the remote control.";i:35;s:98:"If this doesnt fix your problem then the problem is more than likely the safety reversing sensors.";i:36;s:132:"The door closes 6-8 inches and reversesThe door does not close but the motor clicksThe motor hums for 1-2 seconds and does not move.";i:37;s:33:"Manually open and close the door.";i:38;s:90:"Check for binding or obstructions like a broken spring or door lock and correct as needed.";i:39;s:70:"Check the wiring connections at the travel module and the logic board.";i:40;s:110:"This message is an indication that the battery in the door sensor is low and the battery needs to be replaced.";i:41;s:83:"After replacing the battery in your door sensor it can take up to 6 openings and c.";i:42;s:90:"Troubleshooting Guide for Connecting Your myQ Smart Garage Control to the myQ Door Sensor.";i:43;s:107:"You might damage the motor of your garage door opener if there is a lot of resistance from the door tracks.";i:44;s:90:"Locate the Manual Force Adjustment dials at the back of the LiftMaster garage door opener.";i:45;s:31:"They are usually blue in color.";i:46;s:44:"Increase the Opening Force setting slightly.";i:47;s:67:"Now try opening the garage door once again with the remote control.";i:48;s:91:"First disconnect the garage door opener from the garage door by pulling the emergency cord.";i:49;s:99:"Slowly lift the garage door manually and pay attention to the areas where the door binds or sticks.";i:50;s:89:"Inspect the garage door tracks and rollers where the door sticks for any signs of damage.";i:51;s:63:"Fix any dent on the tracks and replace any worn out if you can.";i:52;s:33:"Open and close the door manually.";i:53;s:104:"A properly balanced door will stay in any point of travel while being supported entirely by its springs.";i:54;s:79:"If it does not disconnect the opener and call professional garage door service.";i:55;s:48:"Do not increase the force to operate the opener.";i:56;s:45:"The opener motor hums briefly then wont work.";i:57;s:28:"The garage door springs arc.";i:58;s:74:"Squeaky Garage Door or Garage Door Grinding Sound When Opening or Closing.";i:59;s:65:"If you hear a garage door grinding noise it could be the rollers.";i:60;s:111:"The door track rollers move each time you open or close the door leading to a lot of movement and causing wear.";i:61;s:77:"This wear could damage the roller surface causing them not to roll correctly.";i:62;s:70:"Plus a poorly installed garage door is unsafe for you and your family.";i:63;s:116:"Something could easily break and the garage door can suddenly fall injuring anyone or damaging anything in its path.";i:64;s:39:"Prevent Your Garage Door From Sticking.";i:65;s:117:"A garage door that sticks on the way up and down is an unnecessary annoyance that can be avoided if you follow these.";}}